  "market_context": "Intraday session where price swept a prior swing high, closed back inside forming a bearish C2, and a 5-minute CISD confirmed the change in state of delivery, setting up a continuation lower into the next day.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst identified a valid bearish C2 closure on the 1-hour chart (sweep of prior high and close below it), confirmed by a lower-time-frame CISD (close below the opening price of the up-close candles that formed the high).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst identified a sweep of a prior swing high on the 1-hour NQ chart followed by a close back inside the prior candle’s range, satisfying the Candle 2 Closure requirement.",
    "Step 2: The analyst located the series of up-close candles that formed the swept high and verified that price closed below their opening price, confirming a Change in State of Delivery (CISD) on the lower timeframe.",
    "Step 3: With both C2 closure and CISD confirmed, the analyst concluded the fractal model was valid and anticipated a continuation lower the next day.",
    "Step 4: The analyst noted the indicator marked this as a valid model, reinforcing the setup for a bearish continuation trade."
  ],
  "outcome": "Continuation lower occurred the next day, as stated: 'And there you can see we get a continuation lower.'",
  "lessons": "A bearish C2 closure alone is insufficient; it must be paired with a lower-time-frame CISD (close below the opening of the up-close candles forming the high) to confirm a valid fractal model and high-probability continuation.",
